<h2 id="_settings">3. Settings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Create a new statistic as described on the <strong><a href="/en/basics/statistics">Statistics</a></strong> page of the manual. The <strong>Tops / Flops</strong> statistic includes the <em><strong>settings</strong></em> described in table 1.</p>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/basics/statistics/general-statistics/item/assets/EN-ENG-Statistik-RennerPenner02-SI.png" alt="EN ENG Statistik RennerPenner02 SI">
</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Image 2: <strong>Tops / Flops</strong> statistic; <strong>settings</strong></em></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following table explains the settings under <strong>Start » Statistics → Type of statistic: Item / Tops / Flops</strong>:</p>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Diagram view</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Type of diagram</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Data table</strong> = An overview of the data in table format</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Export</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>The data for this diagram is exported in a <em><strong>CSV file</strong></em>. The parameters are used as displayed. They are the same parameters as shown in the <strong>Data table</strong> diagram.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Raw data export</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>This also generates a <em><strong>CSV file</strong></em>. However, more detailed data is exported. For example, instead of simply indicating the number of orders that were generated on a specific day, the CSV file includes relevant data fields for each individual order, such as the <strong>order ID</strong>, <strong>price</strong> etc.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Settings</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Name</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>The <em><strong>name</strong></em> of the statistic that was entered when the statistic was created. The name can be changed here.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Time span</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a time span for the statistic from the drop-down menu. Default value: <strong>the current week</strong>.<br>
Select a different time span if you do not see any data or if you do not see enough data. Then click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to display the result.<br>
Choosing a <em><strong>larger time span</strong></em> will give you more information. If there is a lot of data, then a <em><strong>shorter time span</strong></em> may make more sense in order to be able to actually interpret the graphic.<br>
If you choose the setting <strong>Date selection</strong>, then please note that data will not be included in the analysis if it is more than <em><strong>6 months old</strong></em>. This is also true for the <em><strong>data export</strong></em> (section 4).</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Starting date / Ending date</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>You can enter a specific <em><strong>starting and ending date</strong></em> here instead of selecting a <strong>time span</strong> (optional).</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Date based on</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select which event should be used for analyzing the data: <strong>Order received</strong>, <strong>Incoming payment</strong> or <strong>Outgoing items</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>From status / To status</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Depending on the type of statistic there are different options available to narrow down the <strong>status</strong>. There are <em><strong>standard values</strong></em> set by default.<br>
<em><strong>All types of orders</strong></em> are included in the statistical analysis except for <em><strong>cancellations</strong></em>. This means that <em><strong>status 8</strong></em> and <em><strong>8.1</strong></em> are excluded from the statistic.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Producer</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the <em><strong>producer</strong></em> that you would like to include into the statistic. Select <strong>All</strong> to include all of the producers. Select <strong>None</strong> if you do not want to include any producers in the statistic.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Client (store)</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the <em><strong>stores</strong></em> that you would like to include into the statistic.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Item referrer</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select the <em><strong>item referrers</strong></em> that you would like to include into the statistic.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Display subcategories of</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>If needed, select which item categories should be displayed along with their subcategories.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Include items without any sales</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark if you want to include items that were not sold at all (<strong>Item quantity</strong> = 0).</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Classify items by attributes</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark to analyze each attribute individually. If you do not place a check mark, then all of an item’s attributes will be grouped together.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Based on</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select whether tops or flops should be displayed in the statistic.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Subtract transportation costs</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark if you don’t want the transportation costs to be taken into consideration for the items.<br>
The costs related to <strong>transportation</strong>, <strong>warehouse</strong>, <strong>operating</strong> and <strong>customs</strong> are only relevant if you saved this information about your items in the <strong>Base</strong> tab.<br>
If you saved information about these costs, then they can be displayed in the statistic and can give you a more detailed overview of your profits and losses.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Subtract payment commission</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark if you don’t want the payment commission to be taken into consideration for the items.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Subtract producer commission</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark if you don’t want the producer commission to be taken into consideration for the items.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Subtract warehouse costs</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark if you don’t want the warehouse costs to be taken into consideration for the items.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Subtract operating costs</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark if you don’t want the operating costs to be taken into consideration for the items.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Subtract customs</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark if you don’t want the customs to be taken into consideration for the items.<br>
The operating and customs costs are saved as percentages.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Inactive items</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Place a check mark to display inactive items.<br>
An item is inactive if a check mark was placed next to the <strong>Inactive</strong> option within the <strong>Available</strong> tab.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Country of delivery</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a country of delivery if you only want to display the items that are sent in this country. Select "All" if you want to display the items that are sent in all countries of delivery.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><em>Table 1: <strong>editing a statistic</strong>; <strong>settings</strong></em></p>
</div>
