<h2 id="_data_export">4. Data export</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>As described in table 1, you can choose between a simple and a detailed export. Examples are displayed below.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_exporting_the_diagram_data">4.1. Exporting the diagram data</h3>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Data fields</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>ItemID</strong> = Item ID, <strong>ItemName</strong> = Item name, <strong>AttributeValueSetID</strong> = Item variant ID, SoldItems = Number of sold items, <strong>PurchasePrice</strong> = Purchase price, <strong>NetPrice</strong> = Net price, <strong>GrossPrice</strong> = Gross price, <strong>StockCosts</strong> = Warehouse costs, <strong>TransportationCosts</strong> = Transportation costs, <strong>Customs</strong> = Customs, <strong>OperationgCosts</strong> = Operating costs, <strong>ProducerCommission</strong> = Producer commission, <strong>PaymentCommission</strong> = Payment commission, <strong>ContributionMarginTwo</strong> = Contribution margin II, <strong>ContributionMarginOne</strong> = Contribution margin I</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
